{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.051Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fine-tuning continues training on a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "smaller, task-specific dataset",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to adapt a pre-trained model. For agents, fine-tuning can teach domain terminology, company policies, preferred tool formats, or multi-turn support patterns—beyond what prompting alone reliably achieves."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Starting from pre-trained weights "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\theta_0"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", optimize on dataset "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\mathcal{D}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with the same (or related) loss as pre-training—typically causal LM on demonstration conversations or completions. Full fine-tuning updates all parameters; parameter-efficient methods (LoRA) update low-rank adapters only."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "General instruct models follow broad alignment; enterprise agents often need consistent tone, internal API shapes, and refusal rules. Fine-tuning embeds these patterns in weights, reducing prompt length and failure rate versus long system prompts alone."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "attrs": {
          "start": 1,
          "type": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Curate high-quality examples: user messages, ideal assistant replies, tool calls"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Format with the model's chat template (roles, special tokens)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Train for a few epochs with low learning rate to avoid catastrophic forgetting"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluate on held-out scenarios; compare to baseline instruct model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"messages\": [\n  {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You call tools via JSON.\"},\n  {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Refund order 8812.\"},\n  {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"\",\n   \"tool_calls\": [{\"name\": \"refund_order\", \"arguments\": {\"order_id\": \"8812\"}}]}\n]}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Higher consistency on repeated agent tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Can distill proprietary workflows into the model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pairs well with RAG—fine-tune behavior, retrieve facts"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Risk of overfitting small datasets"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Catastrophic forgetting of general capabilities if pushed too hard"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Data labeling cost and privacy review for conversation logs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Full FT expensive; LoRA cheaper but may cap peak quality"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to fine-tune vs prompt"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fine-tune: stable format, many similar trajectories, proprietary style"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt only: rare tasks, rapidly changing APIs, prototyping"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RAG: factual knowledge that changes frequently"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fine-tuning adapts pre-trained weights with supervised data"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use chat-formatted trajectories including tool calls for agents"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Low LR and early stopping protect general abilities"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Combine with instruction tuning and alignment stages for production agents"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
